    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-02T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="661"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/6337: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-02T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 2, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>388. Second Chamber Supreme Court today unanimously upheld project of decision
                    submitted by Justice Asiain in petroleum <hi rend="italic">amparo</hi>.<note
                        n="56" xml:id="d661fn56">Cia. Mexieana de Petróleo “El Aguila,” S. A. y
                        coags., Mexico, <hi rend="italic">Semanario Judicial de la Federation</hi>,
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">lxii</hi>, No. 12, November 27–December 2, 1939,
                        pp. 3021–3072; No. 13, December 2–6, 1939, pp. 3073–3184. Published in
                        English in Standard Oil Company of New Jersey, <hi rend="italic">Denials of
                            Justice</hi> (New York, 1940), pp. 49–167.</note> Project of decision
                    was forwarded Department in despatch No. 9518, November 17, 1939.<note n="57"
                        xml:id="d661fn57">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
